An entity to define trade quantity

[TypeConverter(typeof(Quantity.TypeConverter))]
[ObjectSerializer(typeof(Quantity.ObjectSerializer))]
public readonly struct Quantity : IEquatable<Quantity>, IEquatable<int>, IEquatable<double>, IEquatable<decimal>, IComparable, IComparable<Quantity>, IComparable<int>, IComparable<double>, IComparable<decimal>, IComparable<SignedQuantity>, IFormattable

Remarks

Quantity cannot be negative. Actually, in trading quantity is usually used along with TradeAction to specify the direction of trade SignedQuantity to combine these 2 parameters in one value

Parse(string, IFormatProvider?)

Converts the string representation of a number to its Quantity equivalent using the specified culture-specific format information.

public static Quantity Parse(string s, IFormatProvider? provider)

Parameters

s string

The string representation of the number to convert.

provider IFormatProvider

An IFormatProvider that supplies culture-specific parsing information about s.

Returns

Quantity

The Quantity number equivalent to the number contained in s as specified by provider.

Exceptions

ArgumentNullException

s is null.

FormatException

s is not of the correct format.

OverflowException

s represents a number less than MinValue or greater than MaxValue.
